'''Kylantha''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] from [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. She was elected [[Monarch of Naboo/Legends|Monarch of Naboo]] after her predecessor, [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Apailana/Legends|Apailana]], was [[Death/Legends|killed]] on the orders of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] for [[Treason/Legends|treason]] shortly after the [[Declaration of a New Order]]. Formally styled '''Her Highness, Queen Kylantha''', she was installed as a puppet monarch by the Empire and ruled during most of the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]]. Nevertheless, she never became a blind servant of the Galactic Empire and showed sympathy to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Biography==
===Puppet monarch===
{{Quote|Queen Kylantha is now completely devoted to me, which is as it should be.|[[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], to an Imperial spacer|<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />}}
Kylantha was elected [[Monarch of Naboo/Legends|Queen of Naboo]] during the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial era]].<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /> She succeeded [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Apailana/Legends|Apailana]]<ref name="SWCE">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia]]''</ref> in [[18 BBY/Legends|18 BBY]],<ref name="MCkitE">{{Blog|holocron|22/comments|Movie Characters killed in the EU}}</ref> after the latter was [[Battle of Naboo (Imperial Period)|executed]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] for harboring [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] survivors of [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]].<ref name="Battlefront II">''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]''</ref> Although Kylantha was the [[Democracy/Legends|democratically]]-elected head of state of the [[Naboo system/Legends|Naboo system]],<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /> her action as a monarch was overseen by Imperial supervisors.<ref name="Insider82">{{InsiderCite|82|Ask Lobot|Ask the Master}}</ref> Hence, her elections restored [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]'s allegiance to the the Empire<ref name="DB-Apailana">{{DB|character|queenapailana|Apailana, Queen}}</ref> and Queen Kylantha was soon considered as a puppet monarch.<ref name="SWCE" /> In reality, Kylantha's loyalty to the Empire was much more ambiguous.<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /><ref name="SWG:Ttqa" /><ref name="SWG:TEatQ" /><ref name="TRoD">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: The Ruins of Dantooine]]''</ref> After her accession to the [[Throne/Legends|throne]], Kylantha was supposed to reform the Naboo institutions inherited from the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. However, although the queen was outwardly loyal to the Empire, she refused to dissolve the [[Naboo Royal Advisory Council/Legends|Naboo Royal Advisory Council]] and had only implemented a few changes to Naboo's democratic system.<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /> Over the years, Queen Kylantha's mistrust towards the Empire continued to grow.<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" /><ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />

Queen Kylantha resided in the [[Theed Royal Palace/Legends|Royal Palace]] located in the Naboo [[Capital/Legends|capital]] city of [[Theed/Legends|Theed]].<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" /> Like her predecessors,<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref><ref name="AotC">{{Film|II}}</ref> she was served by [[Naboo Royal Handmaidens/Legends|handmaidens]],<ref name="SWGTCG">{{SWGTCG|set=Threat of the Conqueror|cardname=Royal Handmaiden}}</ref>  including [[Teckla Minnau/Legends|Teckla Minnau]],<ref name="DB-Minnau">{{DB|character|teckla|Minnau, Teckla}}</ref> [[Jaanie]]<ref name="SWG:BN" /> and [[Altah]].<ref name="SWG:TE">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=static|The Emperor|Naboo}}</ref>

At some point during her reign, a young and wealthy suitor, in an attempt to win her heart in [[Marriage/Legends|marriage]], purchased a quadrant of the [[Naboo system/Legends|Naboo system]]. However, Kylantha politely refused his offer, saying that she had "married" her people and wished to serve them with all of her [[Time/Legends|time]]. Heartbroken, the suitor renamed the quadrant "[[Kylantha's Whim]]."<ref name="SWG:KW">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=space_poi|Kylantha's Whim|Naboo system}}</ref>

===Galactic Civil War===
{{Quote|The Grand Admiral is stationed inside the palace walls of that treacherous woman. I still am not sure why the Emperor has allowed her to continue to rule and not turned her over to me. Regardless, I am sure he has his reasons.|[[Grand Inquisitor/Legends|Grand Inquisitor]] [[Ja'ce Yiaso]], to an Imperial pilot|<ref name="SWG:GIJY">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=conversation|Grand Inquisitor Ja'ce Yiaso|Naboo}}</ref>}}
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] between the Galactic Empire and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], Queen Kylantha still publicly supported the Empire and was said to be extremely devoted to [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]].<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /> Inwardly, she had become a Rebel sympathizer. After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], she began to communicate secretly with a Rebel [[General/Legends|general]] based on Naboo named [[Jacen Nire]].<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" /> However, her actions led some Imperials, including [[Grand Inquisitor/Legends|Grand Inquisitor]] [[Ja'ce Yiaso]],<ref name="SWG:GIJY" /> [[High Inquisitor]] [[Mal Sikander]],<ref name="SWG:BN">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=static|Boss Nass|Naboo}}</ref> and [[Chief Inquisitor]] [[Loam Redge]], to be highly suspicious.<ref name="TRoD" /> 

Following the Battle of Yavin, the queen invited every years the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] [[Chief/Legends|Chief]] [[Chirpa/Legends|Chirpa]] and his tribe to come to Naboo to celebrate the [[Festival of Love|Ewok Festival of Love]].<ref name="EFoL1">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67596&month=022008|text=Friday Feature – Celebrate the Love}}</ref><ref name="EFoL2">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=68218&month=022009|text=''Star Wars'' Galaxies: Game Update 7}}</ref><ref name="EFoL3">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=68623&month=022010|text=Friday Feature – The Ewok Festival of Love}}</ref><ref name="EFoL4">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=69068&month=022011|text=Weekly Feature – Ewok Festival of Love Highlights}}</ref> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> [[Mikdanyell Guh'rantt]], the [[Mayor/Legends|mayor]] of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], contacted Kylantha and several regional [[Governor/Legends|governors]] across [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] about the increasing commotion that plagued his city. It turned out that this problem did not concern only Mos Eisley. Kylantha, Guh'rantt, and the others eventually agreed to work together to put an end to that nuisance.<ref name="Keeping the Peace">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67406&month=082007|text=Friday Feature &ndash; Keeping the Peace}}</ref>

====Wookiee rescue====
{{Quote|Have you heard of the planet Kashyyyk? It's the home planet of the Wookiee species. I employed some of the Wookiees to investigate the disturbing news of slavery on the planet.|Queen Kylantha, to a Rebel spacer|<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" />}}
Some time after the Battle of Yavin, Queen Kylantha was concerned about [[Slavery/Legends|slavery]] occurring on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]]. She therefore dispatched the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]] [[Orrekazzapirr]], [[Drrlirm]], and [[Imarrra]] to their homeworld to investigate whether the Imperial force stationed on Kashyyyk was [[Enslavement of Kashyyyk|assisting]] the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] [[Slavery/Legends|slavers]].<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" /> In 1 ABY,<ref name="SWG_timeline" /> when she did not receive any news from the Wookiees, Kylantha grew worried. However, a spacer arrived in [[Theed/Legends|Theed]] that Kylantha had heard many stories about from some of her staff but ignored that the spacer was in fact affiliated with the Rebel Alliance. The adventurer agreed to fly to Kashyyyk and investigate the whereabouts of the Wookiees. The Queen had chosen the right being: not only did the adventurer find Drrlirm in the Kashyyykian jungles and escort him to [[Kachirho/Legends|Kachirho]], but tracked the other two Wookiees to the [[Dathomir Imperial Prison|Imperial prison]] on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]] where they had been brought. The Rebel operative helped them escape from the planet through the [[Blockade of Dathomir|Imperial blockade]]. As a token of her appreciation for the help, Kylantha presented the adventurer with an old, rehauled [[Aggressive ReConnaissance-170 starfighter/Legends|ARC-170 starfighter]].<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" />

====The Emperor and the Queen====
{{Quote|Queen Kylantha is dangerously close to betraying her Emperor. But in my overly magnanimous mood, I would like to show her that the Empire is her friend.|Emperor Palpatine, to an Imperial spacer|<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />}}
[[File:Kylantha2.jpg|thumb|Kylantha in her palace during the Galactic Civil War]]
In 1 ABY,<ref name="SWG_timeline" /> a few high-ranking individuals in the Empire, including Emperor Palpatine and Grand Inquisitor Ja'ce Yiaso, were totally certain of the treachery of the queen.<ref name="SWG:GIJY" /> Moreover, the Emperor came to believe that Kylantha was directly in contact with the Rebellion. Knowing that trying to force the queen to reveal her treason would not be beneficial for the Empire, Palpatine resorted to alternate means to get rid of the Rebel general. Instead of having her arrested for treason, Palpatine assigned a group of Imperial operatives to help him manipulate the queen without any blame falling on the Empire.<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />

First, the Imperial operatives traveled to the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]] to recruit a group of [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]], the [[Jantsk mercenaries]], in the name of the Emperor. The operatives later raided a small [[Rebel Base (Dantooine)|Rebel base]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] to steal a Rebel [[Datacard/Legends|datadisk]]. An Imperial agent then [[Slicer/Legends|altered]] the disk and uploaded new data that implicated the Rebel Alliance in an alleged plot against the queen. Afterwards, the Jantsk mercenaries attacked the Theed Royal Palace, posing as Rebel [[Assassin/Legends|assassins]]. Palpatine's agents discreetly assisted the mercenaries in the attack on Kylantha's chambers by ridding the queen of her [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|security guards]]. Eventually, the "assault" failed when [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] arrived in the palace. The Imperial operatives subsequently went to talk to Queen Kylantha, who was not convinced by Vader of the Rebel Alliance's guilt. As "proof" of this, an operative gave Kylantha the falsified datadisk. The queen claimed to be shocked that the Rebels made a personal attack on her and she revealed the location of the Rebel general to the Imperials.<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />

The Imperial operatives eventually proceeded to attack General Jacen Nire's camp, outside the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Dee'ja Peak/Legends|Dee'ja Peak]], killing the Rebel general in the strike. In addition, the Imperial assaulted the [[Mercenary Bunker|Jantsk mercenary bunker]] on Endor where they killed the mercenary leader [[Vurrha Jantsk]] in order to destroy any proof of the implication of the Empire in the attack of the queen. In the end, Emperor Palpatine's plan proceeded exactly as he had foreseen. Queen Kylantha profoundly apologized for her misgivings and gave her full support to the Emperor.<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />

===Legacy===
Prior to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Queen [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Amidala]] amended the Naboo constitution to limit the rule of elected monarchs<ref name="ASD">{{Tales|5|A Summer's Dream}}</ref> to two four-year terms.<ref name="AOTCn">[[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' novelization]]</ref> However, unlike her predecessors, Queen Kylantha substantially exceeded her two terms of office.<ref name="time">According to the sources above-mentioned, Queen Kylantha ruled at least from [[18 BBY/Legends|18 BBY]] to [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]].</ref> Eventually, Kylantha was replaced by another queen named [[Mairayni]].<ref name="TEGtW:AC6">[[Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|''Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare'' Author's Cut, Part 6: Showdown at Naboo]] established that Queen Mairayni was the sixth monarch to reign after [[King/Legends|King]] [[Ars Veruna/Legends|Veruna]]. Various sources indicated that Queen Kylantha was the fifth (after [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Amidala]], [[Jamillia/Legends|Jamillia]], [[Neeyutnee/Legends|Neeyutnee]] and [[Apailana/Legends|Apailana]]) and consequently the predecessor of Mairayni.</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Oh dear! We face a crisis in the court. You, please! On a recent trip to the countryside, we misplaced our special ceremonial makeup. We must have our cosmetics, so as to wear the "scar of remembrance" on our lower lip. Will you bring the kit to us?|Queen Kylantha in a cut quest from ''Star Wars Galaxies''|<ref name="SWG:cut">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=other|directory tree files}}</ref>}}
Kylantha appeared as a [[Wikipedia:Non-player character|non-player character]] (NPC) in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Roleplaying game|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref>

Queen Kylantha was extensively mentioned by other NPCs in the original release of the ''Star Wars Galaxies'',<ref name="SWG:BN" /><ref name="SWG:TE" /> and in its associated strategy guides,<ref name="SWGAEDPOSG" /> but she did not properly appear in the game. Unused game files revealed that the queen was intended to appear as a NPC along with her handmaiden [[Liane]] but both were cut from the final game. Kylantha would have proposed three quests to players who had completed all quests given by Liane. Players working for the queen would have been tasked first to retrieve the queen's royal makeup kit, then, to deliver a refusal letter to an invitation sent by Imperial General [[Dorond]] and, eventually, to escort [[Tedric]], the trainer of Kylantha's [[Guarlara/Legends|guarlara]] [[Roistering Spirit]].<ref name="SWG:cut" />

Queen Kylantha was finally added to the game with the release of the expansion pack [[Star Wars Galaxies: Rage of the Wookiees|''Rage of the Wookiees'']] on [[May 5]], [[2005]]. Rebel players could take a quest from her where they had to rescue Wookiee slaves on Dathomir. They received an ARC-170 starfighter as a reward.<ref name="SWG:Ttqa" /> Later, with the release of the "[[W:c:swg:Update Notes 6.12: September 13 2007|Chapter 6.12]]" update, on [[September 13]], [[2007]],<ref name="SonyCite-Chapter 6.12: Masters of the Wild">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67417&month=092007|text=Chapter 6.12: Masters of the Wild}}</ref> the queen was made a protagonist of the revamped "[[W:c:swg:Imperial Theme Park|Imperial Theme Park]]."<ref name="SWG:TEatQ" />

According to the now-defunct [[StarWars.com]] [[Databank (original)|Databank]], Teckla Minnau, a loyal servant of the deceased Queen Amidala, survived the Clone Wars and returned to Naboo, where she eventually served as a handmaiden to Kylantha.<ref name="DB-Minnau" /> However, her fate was changed in [[2014]] by "[[An Old Friend]]," an episode of ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', which established that Minnau died during the Clone Wars.<ref name="An Old Friend">{{TCW|An Old Friend}}</ref>

